excerpt: 17,000-seat stadium hosts shows, concerts & sporting events including Hockey games.
detail_description: The Honda Center, a 17,000-seat stadium located in Anaheim, California, is a versatile venue that hosts a variety of events including hockey games featuring the Anaheim Ducks. Beyond sports, it is also known for hosting live concerts with major headlining tours and big names like The Weekend, James Taylor, and Michael Buble gracing its stage. Additionally, the center has been home to comedy shows and festivals.
name: Honda Center
address: 2695 E Katella Ave, Anaheim, CA 92806, USA

excerpt: Major League Baseball stadium for the Angels with seats for 45,000+ fans & several restaurants.
detail_description: Angel Stadium, located in Anaheim, is the home of the Los Angeles Angels, offering seating for over 45,000 fans and featuring various restaurants within its premises. Baseball enthusiasts can catch a game during the regular season from late March to early October or opt for public tours on specific dates. The stadium also hosts special events such as family days, fireworks nights, and military appreciation games.
name: Angel Stadium
address: 2000 E Gene Autry Way, Anaheim, CA 92806, USA

excerpt: Upscale food court with local vendors & bars in a renovated, historic 1919 citrus-packing house.
detail_description: The Anaheim Packing District is a trendy food court located just a short distance from Disneyland. Housed in a renovated 1919 citrus-packing house, it features over 30 food stalls and restaurants offering a diverse range of cuisines, including grilled cheese, ramen, Cajun seafood, organic curry, and more. The district's historic buildings have been transformed into spaces for local vendors and bars such as Monkish Brewing, Umami Burger, Unsung Brewing Company, and Pali Wine Company.
name: Anaheim Packing District
address: 440 S Anaheim Blvd, Anaheim, CA 92805, USA

excerpt: Mile-wide park adjacent to the Santa Ana River has 140 acres of picnic tables, lakes, trails & more.
detail_description: Yorba Regional Park, located near the Santa Ana River in Anaheim, is a popular natural attraction. Spanning 140 acres, it features four large lakes with connecting streams, over 400 picnic tables, 200 barbeques, walking and cycling trails, volleyball courts, horseshoe pits, playgrounds, fitness areas and more. This green oasis also offers bike rentals for exploring its biking and jogging paths as well as equestrian trails.
name: Yorba Regional Park
address: 7600 E La Palma Ave, Anaheim, CA 92807, USA

excerpt: This contemporary museum hosts three inventive art exhibits a year & caters to all ages.
detail_description: MUZEO Museum and Cultural Center is a contemporary museum located in Downtown Anaheim, housed within the historic Carnegie library building. The museum hosts three art exhibits annually, appealing to all age groups. It also offers regular live music performances, hands-on art workshops, and other cultural events throughout the year. The primary permanent collection showcases local artists' work, while special exhibitions feature diverse cultural and artistic genres.
name: Muzeo Museum and Cultural Center
address: 241 S Anaheim Blvd, Anaheim, CA 92805, USA

excerpt: Nature park featuring oak forests, scrubland & canyons, plus wildlife & an interpretive center.
detail_description: Oak Canyon Nature Center is a 58-acre natural park located in Anaheim Hills, offering oak forests, scrubland, and canyons to explore. The park features four miles of hiking trails where visitors can spot native wildlife. The John J. Collier Interpretive Center within the park provides an opportunity to learn about the area's natural history through live animal exhibits and educational displays.
name: Oak Canyon Nature Center
address: 6700 E Walnut Canyon Rd, Anaheim, CA 92807, USA

excerpt: Performing arts center with dramatic arched entrance seats 1,700+ for concerts, comedy acts & more.
detail_description: The City National Grove of Anaheim is a state-of-the-art performing arts center with a dramatic arched entrance that can seat over 1,700 people for concerts, comedy acts, and more. It's known for hosting top musical acts from various genres like rock, pop, jazz, blues, and country.
name: Grove of Anaheim
address: 2200 E Katella Ave, Anaheim, CA 92806, USA

excerpt: Classic theme park boasts fast rides, old-fashioned charm & famous fried chicken.
detail_description: Knott's Berry Farm, California's original theme park, offers a mix of fast rides and old-fashioned charm on its 160-acre property. The park features thrilling roller coasters, an authentic 1800s ghost town, and a partnership with the Peanuts characters for meet-and-greets. Visitors can also enjoy seasonal attractions like the Knotts Boysenberry Festival celebrating the farm's berry roots.
name: Knott's Berry Farm
address: 8039 Beach Blvd, Buena Park, CA 90620, USA

excerpt: Children's amusement park for family fun via rides, a petting zoo, an arcade & more.
detail_description: Adventure City is a family-friendly amusement park located in Stanton, offering a variety of rides and attractions for all ages. Unlike the more popular theme parks in the area, Adventure City provides an affordable and less crowded experience. Visitors can enjoy small yet thrilling rollercoasters, a historic carousel from the 1940s, a petting zoo, and even a Thomas the Tank Engine zone for train enthusiasts to design their own tracks.
name: Adventure City
address: 1238 S Beach Blvd, Anaheim, CA 92804, USA

excerpt: Iconic amusement park featuring 8 themed "lands" with rides, shows & costumed characters.
detail_description: Disneyland Park in Anaheim, America's most popular theme park, is a must-visit attraction with its eight themed "lands" offering over 60 major rides, 50 shops, and 30 restaurants. The iconic Sleeping Beauty Castle stands as the landmark of Fantasyland while other original lands like Tomorrowland and Adventureland feature classic attractions such as the Jungle Cruise and Autopia.
name: Disneyland Park
address: Anaheim, CA 92802, USA

excerpt: Contemporary theme park with innovative attractions, multiple dining options & live entertainment.
detail_description: Disney California Adventure Park is a modern theme park with cutting-edge attractions, diverse dining choices, and live performances. It's located within the larger Disneyland Resort in Anaheim. The park features various themed lands such as Hollywood Land, Grizzly Peak, Pacific Wharf, and Cars Land. Visitors can enjoy classic rides like Soarin' Around the World and Radiator Springs Racers. Additionally, there are immersive experiences in areas like Pixar Pier and Avengers Campus.
name: Disney California Adventure Park
address: Anaheim, CA 92802, USA

excerpt: Jousting, horsemanship & falconry plus a 4-course, utensil-free meal served in a castle-like space.
detail_description: Step into a world of chivalry and excitement at Medieval Times Dinner & Tournament, where the spirit of the eleventh century comes alive! This immersive experience features thrilling jousting matches, impressive horsemanship, and breathtaking falconry displays. Guests are treated to a delightful four-course meal served without utensils in a grand castle-like setting. As you dine, watch knights clad in armor compete for glory while horses perform stunning routines that showcase their training and elegance.
name: Medieval Times Dinner & Tournament
address: 7662 Beach Blvd, Buena Park, CA 90620, USA

excerpt: Amusement chain featuring mini golf courses & arcades, some branches with water slides & laser tag.
detail_description: Camelot Golfland is a popular amusement chain that offers a variety of entertainment options for people of all ages. In addition to its renowned mini golf courses, the facility features water slides, laser tag, bumper boats, go-karts, and an arcade. The giant castle at Camelot Golfland is a prominent landmark and sets the stage for an exciting day filled with activities.
name: Camelot Golfland
address: 3200 E Carpenter Ave, Anaheim, CA 92806, USA

excerpt: Children's indoor amusement center for parties includes playground, ball pen & more.
detail_description: Seascape Kids Fun is an award-winning indoor play space designed for children's entertainment and parties. The three-story soft play arena features exciting slides, ball pools, and 13 foam ball air guns for hours of fun. It offers public playtime as well as private party bookings with access to themed dining rooms and the play area. The colorful playground creates an underwater or beachside fantasy universe with various activities centered around playpens, ball pits, and inflatable slides.
name: Seascape Kids Fun
address: 4771 E Hunter Ave, Anaheim, CA 92807, USA

excerpt: Chain of indoor racing centers featuring electric go-karting for all skill levels, plus food.
detail_description: K1 Speed is an indoor racing center that offers electric go-karting suitable for all skill levels. The venue requires participants to be at least 4 feet tall, making it a great option for older kids and adults alike. Prior to racing, all drivers receive a mandatory briefing session to ensure they understand the rules and safety measures. The facility also features a lounge area with comfortable seating and a variety of food options including snacks, pizza, hamburgers, smoothies, beer, and soft drinks.
name: K1 Speed - Indoor Go Karts, Corporate Event Venue, Team Building Activities
address: 1000 N Edward Ct, Anaheim, CA 92806, USA

excerpt: Whimsical, centrally located promenade at Disneyland with shops, restaurants & events.
detail_description: The Downtown Disney District is a vibrant and centrally located promenade at Disneyland, offering an array of shops, restaurants, and entertainment options. Visitors can enjoy a lively nightlife scene with live music and diverse dining experiences. The district features open-air cafes, boutiques, and street performers, making it a must-visit destination within the Anaheim area.
name: Downtown Disney District
address: Anaheim, CA 92802, USA

excerpt: Lush open-air mall with shopping & dining, plus bowling, dance clubs & a live music venue.
detail_description: STC Anaheim GardenWalk is a vibrant open-air mall offering a mix of shopping, dining, and entertainment options. Located just a block away from Disneyland Resort, it has been a popular destination for both tourists and locals for over a decade. The area boasts an array of attractions including the House of Blues Anaheim, known for hosting diverse live music performances that cater to various tastes. Additionally, visitors can enjoy exploring themed shops and indulging in delicious Southern cuisine at the House of Blues Restaurant and Bar.
name: STC Anaheim GardenWalk
address: 321 W Katella Ave, Anaheim, CA 92802, USA

excerpt: Flight simulator for ages 11 & up replicates the feeling of being in a cockpit & flying a plane.
detail_description: Flightdeck is a flight simulation center in California that offers an immersive experience for aviation enthusiasts aged 11 and above. Visitors can pilot a commercial airliner using the Boeing 737 flight simulator or take on the challenges of an Air Force pilot in an authentic military flight simulator. The state-of-the-art facility provides participants with head-to-toe flight suits for added realism. Additionally, Flightdeck features rogue racing simulators that allow guests to race in the world's fastest cars on challenging tracks.
name: Flightdeck + Rogue Racing
address: 400 Disney Way ste 196, Anaheim, CA 92802, USA

detail_description: The Anaheim Packing House, established in 1919 and listed in the National Register of Historic Places in 2015, is a must-visit destination in California. This vibrant food market offers a diverse array of international cuisine from various food stalls housed within its renovated citrus packing house. Visitors can indulge in delicious options such as tacos and sushi while immersing themselves in the lively atmosphere.
name: Anaheim Packing House
address: 440 S Anaheim Blvd, Anaheim, CA 92805, USA

excerpt: High-end restaurant located in a historic old home offers formal Italian dining in a regal setting.
detail_description: Anaheim White House is a high-end restaurant located in a historic old home, offering formal Italian dining in a regal setting. The owner and executive chef, Bruno Serato, is renowned for his philanthropy and fine-dining Italian cuisine. Standout dishes include lobster ravioli, gourmet pizza, and signature steamed salmon 'chocolat.' The restaurant also offers private cellar dining experiences with a five-course feast featuring French-influenced Northern Italian fare.
name: Anaheim White House
address: 887 S Anaheim Blvd, Anaheim, CA 92805, USA
